==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Indebt
<hw>In*debt"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p.
p.</pos> <conjf>Indebted</conjf>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Indebting</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[OE. <ets>endetten</ets>, F.
<ets>endetter</ets>; pref. <ets>en-</ets> (L. <ets>in</ets>) + F.
<ets>dette</ets> debt. See <er>Debt</er>.]</ety> <def>To bring into
debt; to place under obligation; -- chiefly used in the participle
<xex>indebted</xex>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Thy fortune hath <qex>indebted</qex> thee to none.</q>
<rj><qau>Daniel.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Indebted</ent>⟦br⟧
